r\u0026gt; \u0026lt;td\u0026gt;Email\u0026lt;/td\u0026gt; \u0026lt;!-- table data --\u0026gt; \u0026lt;td\u0026gt;Tobias\u0026lt;/td\u0026gt; \u0026lt;td\u0026gt;Linus\u0026lt;/td\u0026gt; \u0026lt;/tr\u0026gt; \u0026lt;tr\u0026gt; \u0026lt;td\u0026gt;16\u0026lt;/td\u0026gt; \u0026lt;td\u0026gt;14\u0026lt;/td\u0026gt; \u0026lt;td\u0026gt;10\u0026lt;/td\u0026gt; \u0026lt;/tr\u0026gt; \u0026lt;/table\u0026gt; \u0026lt;!-- lists --\u0026gt; \u0026lt;!-- unordered list --\u0026gt; \u0026lt;ul\u0026gt; \u0026lt;li\u0026gt;Coffee\u0026lt;/li\u0026gt; \u0026lt;li\u0026gt;Tea\u0026lt;/li\u0026gt; \u0026lt;li\u0026gt;Milk\u0026lt;/li\u0026gt; \u0026lt;/ul\u0026gt; \u0026lt;!-- ordered list --\u0026gt; \u0026lt;ol\u0026gt; \u0026lt;li\u0026gt;Coffee\u0026lt;/li\u0026gt; \u0026lt;li\u0026gt;Tea\u0026lt;/li\u0026gt; \u0026lt;li\u0026gt;Milk\u0026lt;/li\u0026gt; \u0026lt;/ol\u0026gt; ","date":1732924800,"expirydate":-62135596800,"kind":"page","lang":"en","lastmod":1732924800,"objectID":"81cd9875949c086b277b6bbc32273a3e","permalink":"http://localhost:1313/hugopapers/post/html/","publishdate":"2024-11-30T00:00:00Z","relpermalink":"/hugopapers/post/html/","section":"post","summary":"w3schools\n\u003c!-- link: --\u003e \u003clink rel=\"icon\" type=\"image/x-icon\" href=\"/images/favicon.ico\"\u003e \u003ca href=\"https://www.w3schools.com\"\u003eVisit W3Schools\u003c/a\u003e \u003c!-- link as image --\u003e \u003ca href=\"default.asp\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"smiley.gif\" alt=\"HTML tutorial\" style=\"width:42px;height:42px;\"\u003e\u003c/a\u003e \u003c!-- link to bookmark --\u003e \u003ch2 id=\"C4\"\u003eChapter 4\u003c/h2\u003e \u003ca href=\"#C4\"\u003eJump to Chapter 4\u003c/a\u003e \u003c!-- image --\u003e \u003cimg src=\"img_girl.jpg\" width=\"500\" height=\"600\" alt=\"Girl in a jacket\"\u003e \u003c!-- style --\u003e \u003cp style=\"color:red;\"\u003eThis is a red paragraph.\u003c/p\u003e \u003cp style=\"background-color:red;\"\u003eThis is a paragraph.\u003c/p\u003e \u003cp style=\"font-family:courier;\"\u003eThis is a paragraph.\u003c/p\u003e \u003cp style=\"font-size:160%;\"\u003eThis is a paragraph.\u003c/p\u003e \u003cp style=\"text-align:center;\"\u003eCentered paragraph.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c!-- title: se ve como tooltip--\u003e \u003cp title=\"I'm a tooltip\"\u003eThis is a paragraph.\u003c/p\u003e \u003chr\u003e \u003c!-- horizontal rule --\u003e \u003cbr\u003e \u003c!-- salto de linea --\u003e \u003cpre\u003eformatted text\u003c/pre\u003e \u003c!-- formatting --\u003e \u003cb\u003e - Bold text \u003c/b\u003e \u003cstrong\u003e - Important text \u003c/strong\u003e \u003ci\u003e - Italic text \u003c/i\u003e \u003cem\u003e - Emphasized text \u003c/em\u003e \u003cmark\u003e - Marked text \u003c/mark\u003e \u003csmall\u003e - Smaller text \u003c/small\u003e \u003cdel\u003e - Deleted text \u003c/del\u003e \u003cins\u003e - Inserted text \u003c/ins\u003e \u003csub\u003e - Subscript text \u003c/sub\u003e \u003csup\u003e - Superscript text \u003c/sup\u003e \u003c!-- colors --\u003e \u003c!-- https://www.w3schools.com/colors/colors_names.asp --\u003e \u003ch1 style=\"background-color:rgb(255, 99, 71);\"\u003e...\u003c/h1\u003e \u003ch1 style=\"background-color:#ff6347;\"\u003e...\u003c/h1\u003e \u003ch1 style=\"background-color:hsl(9, 100%, 64%);\"\u003e...\u003c/h1\u003e \u003ch1 style=\"background-color:rgba(255, 99, 71, 0.5);\"\u003e...\u003c/h1\u003e \u003ch1 style=\"background-color:hsla(9, 100%, 64%, 0.5);\"\u003e...\u003c/h1\u003e \u003c!-- tables --\u003e \u003ctable\u003e \u003ctr\u003e \u003c!-- table row --\u003e \u003cth\u003ePerson 1\u003c/th\u003e \u003c!-- table header --\u003e \u003cth\u003ePerson 2\u003c/th\u003e \u003cth\u003ePerson 3\u003c/th\u003e \u003c/tr\u003e \u003ctr\u003e \u003ctd\u003eEmail\u003c/td\u003e \u003c!-- table data --\u003e \u003ctd\u003eTobias\u003c/td\u003e \u003ctd\u003eLinus\u003c/td\u003e \u003c/tr\u003e \u003ctr\u003e \u003ctd\u003e16\u003c/td\u003e \u003ctd\u003e14\u003c/td\u003e \u003ctd\u003e10\u003c/td\u003e \u003c/tr\u003e \u003c/table\u003e \u003c!-- lists --\u003e \u003c!-- unordered list --\u003e \u003cul\u003e \u003cli\u003eCoffee\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003eTea\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003eMilk\u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ul\u003e \u003c!-- ordered list --\u003e \u003col\u003e \u003cli\u003eCoffee\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003eTea\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003eMilk\u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ol\u003e ","tags":null,"title":"html","type":"post"},{"authors":null,"categories":"linux","content":"w3school\n\u0026lt;!DOCTYPE html\u0026gt; \u0026lt;html\u0026gt; \u0026lt;body\u0026gt; \u0026lt;h1\u0026gt;My First Web Page\u0026lt;/h1\u0026gt; \u0026lt;p\u0026gt;My First Paragraph\u0026lt;/p\u0026gt; \u0026lt;p id=\u0026#34;demo\u0026#34;\u0026gt;\u0026lt;/p\u0026gt; \u0026lt;!-- con innerHTML --\u0026gt; \u0026lt;script\u0026gt; document.getElementById(\u0026#34;demo\u0026#34;).innerHTML = 5 + 6; \u0026lt;/script\u0026gt; \u0026lt;!-- con document.write --\u0026gt; \u0026lt;script\u0026gt; document.write(5 + 6); \u0026lt;/script\u0026gt; \u0026lt;!-- con window alert --\u0026gt; \u0026lt;script\u0026gt; window.alert(5 + 6); \u0026lt;/script\u0026gt; \u0026lt;!-- con console.log F12 para debbuging --\u0026gt; \u0026lt;script\u0026gt; console.log(5 + 6); \u0026lt;/script\u0026gt; \u0026lt;/body\u0026gt; \u0026lt;/html\u0026gt; \u0026lt;!-- variables --\u0026gt; // no se permite guiones // How to create variables: var x; let y; // How to use variables: x = 5; y = 6; let z = x + y; \u0026lt;!-- objetos --\u0026gt; const person = { firstName: \u0026#34;John\u0026#34;, lastName: \u0026#34;Doe\u0026#34;, age: 50, eyeColor: \u0026#34;blue\u0026#34; }; person.lastName; person[\u0026#34;lastName\u0026#34;]; \u0026lt;!-- strings --\u0026gt; let text = `Welcome ${firstName}, ${lastName}!`; \u0026lt;!-- arrays --\u0026gt; const cars = [\u0026#34;Saab\u0026#34;, \u0026#34;Volvo\u0026#34;, \u0026#34;BMW\u0026#34;]; \u0026lt;!-- array.forEach --\u0026gt; \u0026lt;script\u0026gt; const numbers = [45, 4, 9, 16, 25]; let txt = \u0026#34;\u0026#34;; numbers.forEach(myFunction); document.getElementById(\u0026#34;demo\u0026#34;).innerHTML = txt; function myFunction(value, index, array) { txt += value + \u0026#34;\u0026lt;br\u0026gt;\u0026#34;; } \u0026lt;/script\u0026gt; \u0026lt;!-- array.map crea un nuevo array --\u0026gt; const numbers1 = [45, 4, 9, 16, 25]; const numbers2 = numbers1.map(myFunction); function myFunction(value, index, array) { return value * 2; } map [\u0026#34;a\u0026#34;, \u0026#34;b\u0026#34;, \u0026#34;c\u0026#34;].map(x =\u0026gt; x.toUpperCase()) // resultado: [\u0026#34;A\u0026#34;, \u0026#34;B\u0026#34;, \u0026#34;C\u0026#34;] funciones flecha const sumar = (a, b) =\u0026gt; a + b; es igual a: function sumar(a, b) { return a + b; } ","date":1732924800,"expirydate":-62135596800,"kind":"page","lang":"en","lastmod":1732924800,"objectID":"44c7478f1e47c293d19d3573a556c3a6","permalink":"http://localhost:1313/hugopapers/post/javascript/","publishdate":"2024-11-30T00:00:00Z","relpermalink":"/hugopapers/post/javascript/","section":"post","summary":"w3school\n\u003c!DOCTYPE html\u003e \u003chtml\u003e \u003cbody\u003e \u003ch1\u003eMy First Web Page\u003c/h1\u003e \u003cp\u003eMy First Paragraph\u003c/p\u003e \u003cp id=\"demo\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e \u003c!-- con innerHTML --\u003e \u003cscript\u003e document.getElementById(\"demo\").innerHTML = 5 + 6; \u003c/script\u003e \u003c!-- con document.write --\u003e \u003cscript\u003e document.write(5 + 6); \u003c/script\u003e \u003c!-- con window alert --\u003e \u003cscript\u003e window.alert(5 + 6); \u003c/script\u003e \u003c!-- con console.log F12 para debbuging --\u003e \u003cscript\u003e console.log(5 + 6); \u003c/script\u003e \u003c/body\u003e \u003c/html\u003e \u003c!-- variables --\u003e // no se permite guiones // How to create variables: var x; let y; // How to use variables: x = 5; y = 6; let z = x + y; \u003c!-- objetos --\u003e const person = { firstName: \"John\", lastName: \"Doe\", age: 50, eyeColor: \"blue\" }; person.lastName; person[\"lastName\"]; \u003c!-- strings --\u003e let text = `Welcome ${firstName}, ${lastName}!`; \u003c!-- arrays --\u003e const cars = [\"Saab\", \"Volvo\", \"BMW\"]; \u003c!-- array.forEach --\u003e \u003cscript\u003e const numbers = [45, 4, 9, 16, 25]; let txt = \"\"; numbers.forEach(myFunction); document.getElementById(\"demo\").innerHTML = txt; function myFunction(value, index, array) { txt += value + \"\u003cbr\u003e\"; } \u003c/script\u003e \u003c!-- array.map crea un nuevo array --\u003e const numbers1 = [45, 4, 9, 16, 25]; const numbers2 = numbers1.map(myFunction); function myFunction(value, index, array) { return value * 2; } map [\"a\", \"b\", \"c\"].map(x =\u003e x.toUpperCase()) // resultado: [\"A\", \"B\", \"C\"] funciones flecha const sumar = (a, b) =\u003e a + b; es igual a: function sumar(a, b) { return a + b; } ","tags":null,"title":"javascript","type":"post"},{"authors":null,"categories":"linux","content":"lshw\nfree »\u0026gt; ram, swap\nsudo fdisk -l, muestra particiones\nsudo lsblk -no NAME,UUID,LABEL\ndf -h, muestra espacio\ndu -sh directorio, muestra el tamaño del dir\nuname -r , kernel version\ncat /etc/*release\nlspci, lsusb\nmount\nservice –status-all\necho “$XDG_SESSION_TYPE” xorg or wayland\n","date":1732838400,"expirydate":-62135596800,"kind":"page","lang":"en","lastmod":1732838400,"objectID":"849bf31c09f6f8f18c43a3cdce93ec88","permalink":"http://localhost:1313/hugopapers/post/hardware-info/","publishdate":"2024-11-29T00:00:00Z","relpermalink":"/hugopapers/post/hardware-info/","section":"post","summary":"lshw\nfree »\u003e ram, swap\nsudo fdisk -l, muestra particiones\nsudo lsblk -no NAME,UUID,LABEL\ndf -h, muestra espacio\ndu -sh directorio, muestra el tamaño del dir\nuname -r , kernel version\ncat /etc/*release\nlspci, lsusb\nmount\nservice –status-all\necho “$XDG_SESSION_TYPE” xorg or wayland\n","tags":null,"title":"hardware info","type":"post"},{"authors":null,"categories":"linux","content":"r– 4= lectura\n-w- 2= escritura\n–x 1= ejecución\n6 (4+2)= lectura y escritura\n5 (4+1)= lectura y ejecución\n3 (2+1)= escritura y ejecución\n7 (4+2+1)= lectura, escritura y ejecución\nu owner, g group, o others, a all\nr read access, w write access, x execute access\nej chmod g+rw miarchivo.txt\nchmod ugo+x programa.sh\nchmod u=rwx g=rw o=r filename\n","date":1732838400,"expirydate":-62135596800,"kind":"page","lang":"en","lastmod":1732838400,"objectID":"6ef3308a9607b629f4e95a9c295c41b8","permalink":"http://localhost:1313/hugopapers/post/permisos/","publishdate":"2024-11-29T00:00:00Z","relpermalink":"/hugopapers/post/permisos/","section":"post","summary":"r– 4= lectura\n-w- 2= escritura\n–x 1= ejecución\n6 (4+2)= lectura y escritura\n5 (4+1)= lectura y ejecución\n3 (2+1)= escritura y ejecución\n7 (4+2+1)= lectura, escritura y ejecución\nu owner, g group, o others, a all\nr read access, w write access, x execute access\nej chmod g+rw miarchivo.txt\nchmod ugo+x programa.sh\nchmod u=rwx g=rw o=r filename\n","tags":null,"title":"permisos","type":"post"},{"authors":null,"categories":"linux","content":"ps -ef, ps -f -u waltermas , pstree, top\njobs, fg %1 , bg %1\nCTRL+Z, manda el proceso a background\nkill -l, lista todas las señales (mejor parece man kill)\nkill -9 PID (force)\nxkill, killall, pkill\npgrep firefox, devuelve el pid\n","date":1732838400,"expirydate":-62135596800,"kind":"page","lang":"en","lastmod":1732838400,"objectID":"70aa9688c7fd71133e1dbb518f3d5289","permalink":"http://localhost:1313/hugopapers/post/procesos/","publishdate":"2024-11-29T00:00:00Z","relpermalink":"/hugopapers/post/procesos/","section":"post","summary":"ps -ef, ps -f -u waltermas , pstree, top\njobs, fg %1 , bg %1\nCTRL+Z, manda el proceso a background\nkill -l, lista todas las señales (mejor parece man kill)\nkill -9 PID (force)\nxkill, killall, pkill\npgrep firefox, devuelve el pid\n","tags":null,"title":"procesos","type":"post"},{"authors":null,"catego